title: Afrospilarctia unipuncta
text: Afrospilarctia unipuncta is a <a href="moth">moth</a> of the family <a href="Erebidae">Erebidae</a>. It was described by <a href="George%20Hampson">George Hampson</a> in 1905. It is found in <a href="Angola">Angola</a>, the <a href="Democratic%20Republic%20of%20the%20Congo">Democratic Republic of the Congo</a>, <a href="Kenya">Kenya</a>, <a href="Malawi">Malawi</a>, <a href="Rwanda">Rwanda</a>, <a href="Tanzania">Tanzania</a>, <a href="Uganda">Uganda</a> and <a href="Zimbabwe">Zimbabwe</a>.
